dcterms:description: A comprehensive surgical skill dataset developed by the Computational Interaction and Robotics Laboratory at Johns Hopkins University, encompassing kinematic, video, and gesture data from three elementary surgical tasks performed using the da Vinci surgical robot: suturing, knot tying, and needle passing.
